{"abstract":[{"text":"Take advantage of custom decoding and encoding logic for the shared file storage persistence","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"strategy, as well as beta support for Swift’s native Testing framework."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library introduced 1 new","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"API, as well as beta support for Swift Testing."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tools of version 1.11. See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" for more information.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Important","style":"important"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Custom-file-storage-coding","text":"Custom file storage coding"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.10 of the Composable Architecture introduced a powerful tool for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"sharing state"}],"type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"sharing state"},{"type":"text","text":" amongst your features, and included several built-in persistence"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"strategies, including file storage. This strategy, however, was not very flexible, and only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"supported the default JSON encoding and decoding offered by Swift.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In this version, you can now define custom encoding and decoding logic using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage(_:decode:encode:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"Swift Testing","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Swift-Testing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Xcode 16 and Swift 6 come with a powerful new native testing framework. Existing test targets using","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"XCTest can even incrementally adopt the framework and define new tests with Testing. Existing XCTest"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"test ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"helpers","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", however, are not compatible with the new framework, and so test tools like the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Composable Architecture’s "},{"code":"TestStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" did not work with it out of the box.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That changes with this version, which seamlessly supports XCTest "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"and"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Swift’s Testing framework."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can now create a test store in a "},{"code":"@Test","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and failures will be reported accordingly."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.12"]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\